  51. (* data_type is used mainly on memory addressing to specify

  70. ‌type registerf = XMM of int | TOS | ST of int

  72. ‌type arch = X64 | X86

  74. ‌type addr =
  75.   {
  76.     arch: arch;
  77.     typ: data_type;
  78.     idx: reg64;
  79.     scale: int;
  80.     base: reg64 option;
  81.     sym: string option;
  82.     displ: int;
  83.   }
  84.   (** Addressing modes:
  85.       displ + sym + base + idx * scale
  86.       (if scale = 0, idx is ignored and base must be None)
  87.   *)
